<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96654290523815></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96654290523815><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96654290523815>The first bard post!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96654290523815#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=381><span id= >Raventod</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 4:08 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I love playing a bard. I have a 25 musician on Luclin and let me tell you, it's great. You get a new spell every level, are welcome in parties, and your quest items are easy to get because by and large, there are generally very few folks out there who play bards. For every 10 druids there may be one of us.<br><br>We can heal, run fast, become invisible, buff, debuff, clarity, DD, DoT, lull, charm, and levitate, among other things. <br><br>One tip I can give you, party often after level five. Most groups as glad to have you for the healing alone. You can cut your team's downtime in half by getting them back up to full health in a few minutes. <br><br>Be careful in battle. It's okay to melee a bit, but count on baddies going after you because you are singing so loudly. Ensure your tanks know this so they can taunt for you. <br><br>In battle, become a group leader. You can put the mobs to sleep and direct your teammates to attack them methodically. I have helped a full group of 20th take out three red mobs this way without fatalities.<br><br>I have started and nearly finished the entire lambent quest already (again, level 25). Your invis and speed songs can get you deep into dungeons to loot the items off bodies left lying. Most groups will let you take your Lore/Nodrop items becaus they don't need them. A lot of people think I am a twink, and while I have not killed every monster that droped my quest items myself, I have not purchased a single piece of lambent nor have I used another character to complete the quests for me.<br><br>And a full set of Lambent is hands-down the FINEST looking armor in the game.<br><br>Peace, fellows. Fare thee well.<br>&nbsp;<br>Raventod Ivikkewikkae<br>Guildmaster of the Steel Gladiators<br>Luclin Server</td></tr>
